cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper deals with zero-shot learning, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) that aims to recognize objects or classes that have not been seen during training. The paper also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as it deals with word embeddings. The proposed method involves joint learning of visually consistent word vectors and label embedding model, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed approach on benchmark datasets, which involves multimedia (cs.MM) as it deals with visual data.
